Eros International plc - Strategy, SWOT and Corporate Finance Report, is a source of comprehensive company data and information. The report covers the company's structure, operation, SWOT analysis, product and service offerings and corporate actions, providing a 360deg view of the company.Key FindingsDetailed information on Eros International plc required for business and competitor intelligence needsA study of the major internal and external factors affecting Eros International plc in the form of a SWOT analysisAn in-depth view of the business model of Eros International plc including a breakdown and examination of key business segmentsIntelligence on Eros International plc's mergers and acquisitions (MandA), strategic partnerships and alliances, capital raising, private equity transactions, and financial and legal advisorsNews about Eros International plc, such as business expansion, restructuring, and contract winsLarge number of easy-to-grasp charts and graphs that present important data and key trendsReasons to Get this ReportGain understanding of Eros International plc and the factors that influence its strategies.Track strategic initiatives of the company and latest corporate news and actions.Assess Eros International plc as a prospective partner, vendor or supplier.Support sales activities by understanding your customers' businesses better.Stay up to date on Eros International plc's business structure, strategy and prospects.Report HighlightsEros International Plc (Eros) is an international entertainment and integrated media company. It is involved in the acquisition, co-production and distribution of films and related content domestic and globally. The company's services include the production of TV and film content, theatrical, satellite channels and cable services. It distributes film content through distribution channels such as theatrical, television syndication and digital. Eros also owns an entertainment portal, Eros Now, which provides access to over 5,000 movies, and 250,000 audio tracks. The company holds licensing rights to about 3,000 films across Hindi and regional languages. Eros operates in 50 countries with offices in India, the UK, the US, the UAE, Australia, Fiji, and Singapore with 44 million registered users worldwide. It also releases Indian films that are subtitled or dubbed in local languages in Europe and South East Asia. Eros is headquartered in Mumbai, Maharashtra, India.
